===2020 census===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Davenport had a population of 388. The population density was {{convert|136.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Davenport was 243 (62.6%) [[White Americans|White]], 3 (0.8%) [[African Americans|African American]], 13 (3.4%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 3 (0.8%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 53 (13.7%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 73 (18.8%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 152 persons (39.2%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Davenport CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0618086 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 19, 2025}}</ref>

The census reported that 92.5% of the population lived in households, 7.5% lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and no one was institutionalized.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 121 households, out of which 29 (24.0%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 54 (44.6%) were married-couple households, 12 (9.9%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 22 (18.2%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 33 (27.3%) had a male householder with no partner present. 30 households (24.8%) were one person, and 20 (16.5%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.97.<ref name=DP1/> There were 72 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (59.5% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Davenport CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0618086 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 19, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 98 people (25.3%) under the age of 18, 25 people (6.4%) aged 18 to 24, 92 people (23.7%) aged 25 to 44, 108 people (27.8%) aged 45 to 64, and 65 people (16.8%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 40.7{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 100.0 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 140 housing units at an average density of {{convert|49.2|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 121 (86.4%) were occupied. Of these, 76 (62.8%) were owner-occupied, and 45 (37.2%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

